Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.56,0:00:04.98,Ep_Title,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(550,1)}Where To?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.18,0:00:29.69,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"I love animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.69,0:00:33.01,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When I grow up, I want to work at the zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.37,0:00:36.38,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I don't like humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.87,0:00:40.60,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Being around humans makes me anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.21,0:00:43.78,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always told to look people \Nin the eye when I talk to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.78,0:00:45.85,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm too scared to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.64,0:00:50.27,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I hate going to festivals where \Nthere are lots of people, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.27,0:00:55.88,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,My classmates tease me, \N hit me, and laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.40,0:01:00.83,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not good at school or sports, \Nso my teachers won't help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.19,0:01:04.15,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Even the teachers tease me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.08,0:01:08.79,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, I can't stop the tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.79,0:01:12.89,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The harder I try to stop them, \Nthe more they keep coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.34,0:01:17.53,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It's so frustrating and embarrassing,\N I wish I could disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.14,0:01:22.45,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When I cry out loud, \Nmy classmates laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:27.34,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They say I'm like a walrus and laugh at me."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.19,0:01:32.05,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"I wish I were a walrus instead."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.19,0:01:33.48,sign_2115_18_I_wish_I_were_a_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I were a walrus instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.19,0:01:36.05,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"My mom is the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:40.49,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Since Dad never comes home, she's always \Nannoyed and takes it out on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:45.87,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Every day she eats lots of food, \Nand then she hits me and screams at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:50.19,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike at school, I don't cry at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.19,0:01:53.00,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's because my mom cries.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.72,0:01:58.47,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,My dad's never home \Nbecause he has a mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:02.80,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When he does occasionally \Ncome home, he gets blind drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:05.43,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's my dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.43,0:02:09.18,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but he bought me an animal \Nencyclopedia, so I like him okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.90,0:02:13.77,sign_3115_29_Animal_Encyclope,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Animal Encyclopedia
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:13.47,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I never got tired of looking \Nat my animal encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.10,0:02:16.82,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I read lots of animal books at the library,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.82,0:02:19.98,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I like this book \Nmy dad gave me the most."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:24.66,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"There's something else \Nthat I like, too. Cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:28.61,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be okay to get a job \Ndriving cars when I grow up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.99,0:02:33.82,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,On rare occasions, my dad \Ntakes me for a ride in his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.19,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I liked going on drives as a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.19,0:02:39.65,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but these days, my mom doesn't ride with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.18,0:02:46.10,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I think my dad doesn't bring my mom \Nbecause he's going to see his mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:52.07,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He tells me, 'Hiroshi, don't tell your \Nmother,' and leaves me at the zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:57.18,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for my mom, \Nbut I loved my time at the zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:02.41,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't look people in the eye, but I could \Nstare into the eyes of animals forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.01,0:03:08.29,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't speak to people, \Nbut I could speak to animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.73,0:03:10.37,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I saw a walrus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:16.96,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They make funny sounds \Nand they're fat, just like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:21.04,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they looked like my mom, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.72,0:03:25.58,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When I think about returning \Nto reality with all its humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.18,0:03:28.64,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather stay here forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.21,0:03:45.88,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why that day, on the day \Nof the accident, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:44.37,sign_5335_51_National_Traffic,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,National Traffic Safety Campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.25,0:03:51.21,Default,MC,0000,0000,0000,,The loser's bracket group \Nthat will be advancing to the finals
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:54.50,sign_5544_54_Losers__Bracket,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Losers' Bracket
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:55.36,Default,MC,0000,0000,0000,,is entry number 1770, Rush Style!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:59.20,Default,ENTERTAINER,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What? Really?! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.37,0:04:00.01,Default,ENTERTAINER,0000,0000,0000,,We did it, Nozuyama-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.01,0:04:04.34,sign_5755_57_N_1_Grand_Prix__,SIGN TOP LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,N-1 Grand Prix\N {\c&Hc1bd89&}2021 {\c&H5ee0d5&}Losers' Bracket
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.01,0:04:04.34,Italics,ENTERTAINER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy. I'm already writing jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.34,0:04:06.73,Default,AUDIENCE B,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently Donraku-san stepped down \Nfrom the judge's panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.73,0:04:09.89,Default,AUDIENCE A,0000,0000,0000,,What else would he do? His daughter died.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.92,Italics,MC,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.92,Default,AUDIENCE B,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, can we change the channel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:13.81,Italics,ENTERTAINER,0000,0000,0000,,We'll ride this wave all the way to—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:16.48,sign_6086_64_Live__Private_Ta,SIGN TOP RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,Live: Private Taxi Speeding Down {\c&H000000&}Expressway
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:22.03,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-san's not answering his phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.03,0:04:23.96,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Where is that taxi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:27.37,Italics,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It's heading towards \Nthe harbor from Toranomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.37,0:04:29.68,Italics,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. I'll head there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:33.16,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Take me with you, Dr. Goriki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:47.60,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, a high school listener \Nwas waiting for me to come outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.60,0:04:49.43,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me to team up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.51,0:04:53.27,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,He must be disappointed after \Nwatching that loser's bracket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.27,0:04:56.03,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,All we did was scream insults at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.96,0:05:00.41,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you really want to split up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.41,0:05:03.74,Default,BABA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who said we should split up \Nif we didn't make it this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:05.74,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We were so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:08.29,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If we quit after I forgot our jokes, \Nall I'd have left would be regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.29,0:05:10.95,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Next year will be our last year. \NWon't you reconsider?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.89,0:05:15.47,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.47,0:05:17.50,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to be my straight man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.50,0:05:19.77,Default,BABA,0000,0000,0000,,You always said I was a crap straight man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.89,0:05:20.46,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:22.51,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll write funnier jokes. \NBe my straight man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.51,0:05:24.67,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Interrupt me again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:33.43,Flashback_Italics,YAMAMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,The police will probably \Nkeep questioning us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.79,0:05:35.20,Flashback,YAMAMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,We should get our story straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:38.65,Flashback,NIKAIDO,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't we just tell them the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.65,0:05:42.78,Flashback,YAMAMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,The{\i1} truth?{\i0} Do you understand what we did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:05:58.29,Flashback_Italics,GIRL A,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever seen her house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:06:01.58,Flashback,GIRL B,0000,0000,0000,,It's an obvious prefab packed to the brim, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.58,0:06:04.92,Flashback,GIRL A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They say that's why she \Nspends all her time in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:07.17,Default,GIRL B,0000,0000,0000,,That's hilarious. I bet she gets super wrinkly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:08.38,sign_8750_92_My_Dream_For_the,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,My Dream For the Future
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:08.38,sign_8750_93_Super_Rich,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Super Rich
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.70,0:06:21.69,Flashback_Italics,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:23.11,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:24.17,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,Have you eaten dinner yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:27.87,Flashback,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, but you must be tired \Nfrom work, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:29.42,Flashback,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:33.11,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,You'll need a lunch for tomorrow. \NI'll make dinner while I'm at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.11,0:06:34.56,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have fried chicken, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:36.93,Flashback,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.53,0:06:42.20,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,As someone whose dreams were \Nshattered, you look radiant to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.20,0:06:44.21,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,You only get one go around in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.21,0:06:47.50,Flashback,MOM,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta do whatever it takes \Nto make your dreams come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:20.13,Default,TANAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I have nothing left. It's game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:27.50,sign_10658_107_Ksawa___Ksawa_2d,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ksawa\N {\c&H7b7b7b&\fs14\b0}@Ksawa_2daime
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.50,0:07:32.01,sign_10730_108_Ksawa,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Ksawa
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.50,0:07:32.01,sign_10658_109_I_was_shocked_to,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,I was shocked to learn that Donraku's daughter \Nis the dead Mystery Kiss girl and I feel bad \Nfor them, but how I'm going to support myself \Nfrom now on is the bigger, more serious mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.20,Default,YANO,0000,0000,0000,,Hit him again! Again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:45.52,sign_11113_111_Road_Closed,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Road Closed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.76,0:07:53.87,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure out what \NOdokawa-san's illness is called?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.87,0:07:57.26,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's called...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.18,0:08:03.14,Flashback,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,Visual agnosia caused \Nby executive dysfunction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:06.71,Flashback,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Visual agnosia...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.54,0:08:09.11,Italics,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.11,0:08:12.55,Italics,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't know what \Nhis eyes are looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:17.05,Italics,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damage to his brain is causing \Nan error in its cognitive function.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.43,0:08:24.77,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Stop the car, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.41,0:08:42.16,Default,YANO,0000,0000,0000,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:13.44,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shirakawa-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.55,0:09:33.30,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This'll go viral!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:05.40,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Please. One more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:06.91,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Be my straight man one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:11.42,Default,SHIBAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? I'm being interrupted by a car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.68,0:10:43.45,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"That's why that day, \Non the day of the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.45,0:10:46.07,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I remember being happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.58,0:10:52.13,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,My mom put my plastered dad in \Nthe car and took us for a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:55.90,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It'd been so long since we'd gone \Nfor a drive as a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:58.07,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,My dad was sleeping in the back seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:01.07,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and my mom seemed like \Nshe was in a bad mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.07,0:11:03.15,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I was having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:06.62,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It was my first night drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.62,0:11:11.27,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The roads and traffic signals and lights \Nof the cars were sparkly and pretty."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.39,0:11:16.43,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"When I woke up, \NI was lying in a hospital bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.84,0:11:20.79,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,My head felt dizzy. I felt weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:25.66,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors explained a bunch of stuff \Nto me, but I don't remember much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:31.50,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,All I remember is that my dad and mom \Nwent somewhere after the accident
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:35.20,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and that the doctor kind of \Nlooked like an alligator,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.13,0:11:39.51,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,since I had actually become a walrus."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:43.54,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"My relatives and teachers showed up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.54,0:11:48.73,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and had serious conversations \Nand told me all kinds of stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.73,0:11:50.77,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't really care.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.14,0:11:56.02,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I met patients and nurses, \Nbut it didn't bother me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:12:02.66,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they were pandas and beavers \Nand tortoises and llamas and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:09.11,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone said they felt sorry for me, \Nbut I was better off than I was before."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.58,0:12:14.58,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,"One day, a tapir showed up \Nand said he'd look after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.21,0:12:18.53,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have to see \Nmy old classmates again,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.53,0:12:20.51,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and I'd get to move to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.51,0:12:22.75,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't imagine anything better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.49,0:12:27.49,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I was really glad that I'd become a walrus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.40,0:12:31.85,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I only met the tapir then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:35.59,Flashback_Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I wanted to go thank him \Nproperly someday."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.10,0:13:01.55,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Queixada!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.32,0:13:12.14,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, over here! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.44,0:13:21.83,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.83,0:13:23.10,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.12,0:13:25.27,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.64,0:13:26.97,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:32.05,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.51,0:13:34.95,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:44.63,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Odokawa. What do I look like to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.73,0:13:47.47,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,A human.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.47,0:13:49.98,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Does that scare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.98,0:13:53.03,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not scared. I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.03,0:13:54.19,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:01.57,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're scared of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:05.20,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No. You're... pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:09.89,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he still can't talk to women.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:33.52,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Your plan ended in failure, Dobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.52,0:14:35.72,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,But don't worry. I'll let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:37.16,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Daimon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:40.83,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding. I'm the younger brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:42.81,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a funny prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.81,0:14:44.25,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.25,0:14:46.09,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,He said only relatives think it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.09,0:14:47.58,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:51.21,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,An officer will be arriving with your arrest \Nwarrant soon. I thought I'd let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.21,0:14:55.04,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you tell me that? What if I run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:58.04,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll shoot you again. Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.21,0:15:01.47,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That shot was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.47,0:15:04.69,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I got in a lot of trouble for it, \Nbut I got to arrest your gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:05.84,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,No big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.84,0:15:08.49,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You know what'll happen if I get arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.49,0:15:09.80,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother will go down, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:13.21,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. After all, \Nwhat my brother did was bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.21,0:15:15.22,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Crimes should be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:19.23,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Evil can never be destroyed completely, \Nbut I'll keep maintaining the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:21.71,Default,KOSHIRO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm a police officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:32.07,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like some jelly? \NOr would you prefer pudding?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.33,0:15:35.66,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough. Just sit. It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:40.66,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yesterday the MPD arrested \NMystery Kiss member Rui Nikaido,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:44.21,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}who they had been questioning \Nin connection to the murder
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:44.21,sign_22554_196_Suspects_Arreste,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Suspects Arrested in Yuki Mitsuya-san Murder\N {\fs20}Body Dumped in Sea After Killing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:48.70,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}of Mystery Kiss member Yuki Mitsuya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:50.41,sign_22639_197_Arrested__Rui_Ni,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested: Rui Nikaido (18)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:50.41,sign_22639_198_Suspected_of_dum,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Suspected of dumping body in the sea after \Nkilling fellow group member at agency office
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:52.85,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Mystery Kiss manager Fuyuki Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:16:01.39,sign_22788_204_Arrested__Unempl,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested: Unemployed \N{\fs20}Togo Sekiguchi {\fs16}(26)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:16:01.39,sign_22788_202_Arrested__Employ,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested: Employee \N{\fs20}Fuyuki Yamamoto{\fs16} (34)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:16:01.39,sign_22788_203_Arrested__Unempl,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Arrested: Unemployed \N{\fs20}Haruhito Yano {\fs16}(28)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.85,0:15:58.63,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Haruhito Yano, unemployed, \Nand Togo Sekiguchi, also unemployed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.63,0:16:01.39,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}were arrested for abandoning a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.39,0:16:05.30,Italics,NEWSCASTER,0000,0000,0000,,Rui Nikaido is denying the charges...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.30,0:16:07.23,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I just remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.23,0:16:08.02,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:11.78,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing. It's got nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.78,0:16:14.41,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're still acting shy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.41,0:16:17.14,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They've been reporting \Non this story since this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:20.57,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-san, you'll probably \Nbe interviewed at some point,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.57,0:16:23.04,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but once things settle down, \NI'd like to go to the zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.04,0:16:25.08,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What? With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:30.87,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I brought someone who said \Nhe wanted to see you, Odokawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.87,0:16:33.97,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-sama, are you feeling all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:36.62,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Thankfully, I'm doing okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.62,0:16:38.29,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's Imai.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.29,0:16:39.90,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.90,0:16:43.56,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, are you okay? That idol...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:45.77,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,It came as a huge shock,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.77,0:16:49.57,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,and if she really did do it, \Nthat would be a terrible thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.57,0:16:53.15,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,but when I think about it, getting to visit \Nan idol in prison is a precious experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.51,0:16:56.03,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're looking at this really positively.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.03,0:16:58.88,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,So once I visit her—even if I don't,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.88,0:17:02.14,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll decide whether or not \NI want to continue supporting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:03.65,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.23,0:17:08.71,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,The police retrieved the money \Nthat fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.71,0:17:11.47,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,I know some of it's missing, \Nbut this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.31,0:17:13.50,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.50,0:17:15.65,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Please, you have to take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.65,0:17:18.68,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,I caused all kinds of trouble for you, \Nand you helped me a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:21.88,Default,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He seems insistent. Why don't you accept it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.88,0:17:25.07,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It can't hurt to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.07,0:17:28.10,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I wouldn't know how to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.10,0:17:30.10,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,You could pay off Kakihana's debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.10,0:17:33.40,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'll make him pay it off himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.40,0:17:35.74,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can think of one use for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.74,0:17:37.56,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll accept it, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.56,0:17:39.68,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.68,0:17:43.08,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a Rui-tan fan meeting to \Ndiscuss what we'll do going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:46.21,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Right. That reminds me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:50.68,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The girl I drove late at night on October 4th \Nto the Mystery Kiss office...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:52.59,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:55.34,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I guess I should tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:17:58.15,Default,IMAI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, goodbye. I'll visit again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.47,0:18:03.72,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,One use? You mean the traffic \Naccident orphan foundation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:05.84,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.84,0:18:10.01,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea \Nwho to return the money to?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.01,0:18:12.27,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure my landlady knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.27,0:18:15.00,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you give it to him yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.00,0:18:17.95,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's a tapir. You know who that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.10,0:18:22.19,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. A tapir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:24.65,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.65,0:18:29.77,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Odokawa, this is hard to say, \Nbut I need to confirm something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.77,0:18:30.75,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:33.58,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,What's inside your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.09,0:18:42.63,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! He's falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.09,0:18:44.43,sign_26880_258_Comedy_Duos_Comp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Comedy Duos Compete to Survive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.09,0:18:44.43,sign_26880_259_Who_Will_Fall_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Who Will Fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.09,0:18:44.43,sign_26880_260_Bonnou_Illuminat,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Bonnou Illumination
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:47.43,sign_26960_261_Yamabiko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yamabiko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.43,0:18:49.44,sign_27032_262_Reserved_for_the,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Reserved for the day\N{\fs18}-Yamabiko
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.56,0:19:00.55,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,You all better now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.19,0:19:05.61,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I was always healthy. I can sleep now, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.61,0:19:07.28,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:14.87,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Confidently speaking to a human like you \Nis a huge step forward for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.87,0:19:17.19,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still not comfortable \Naround women, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.19,0:19:19.00,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:22.36,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The police haven't arrested you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.36,0:19:25.21,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I have \Nexceptional subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.21,0:19:29.04,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure a lot of people \Nsuffered because of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.04,0:19:31.81,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm not here to criticize you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.81,0:19:37.24,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my job, and you've probably \Nsaved more people than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:39.35,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.89,0:19:42.55,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,Not only did I fail to save \NDon-chan's daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:44.14,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,but my subordinates were involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.14,0:19:46.49,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about putting the cart \Nbefore the horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.49,0:19:50.71,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Dobu \Nthat you have only one rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:55.92,Default,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. "Don't kill people." That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.21,0:19:58.58,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:05.01,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,There's close to 100 million yen in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.01,0:20:07.32,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to do as much as you can with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.32,0:20:09.84,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's just helping the kids \Nyou're currently supporting,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.84,0:20:13.94,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,don't tell them until \Nyou give them that doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:19.33,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You've been a great help \Nuntil now. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:58.27,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Great. It's just a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.03,0:21:02.54,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get started. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.54,0:21:03.94,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,We're Bonnou Illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.94,0:21:05.82,Italics,FUKUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,We sure did get roped into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.82,0:21:08.32,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We're pinch-hitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.32,0:21:09.31,Italics,FUKUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,For Homosapiens.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.31,0:21:10.83,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:12.16,Italics,FUKUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing wrong \Nwith saying their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.16,0:21:13.99,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,Right. It's okay to mention their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.99,0:21:16.34,Italics,FUKUTOMO,0000,0000,0000,,Can you believe Baba-san \Nwas dating a murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.34,0:21:17.68,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.68,0:21:19.57,Italics,FUKUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone will creeped out unless I say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.57,0:21:21.42,Italics,KONDO,0000,0000,0000,,She's still only a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:25.12,Italics,FUKUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about that. We're here \Nto produce a proper radio show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:28.00,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.00,0:21:31.68,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I transferred to a bigger agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:34.86,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Things are going so \Nwell, it's almost scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.86,0:21:39.27,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I hounded the manager \Nafter I failed an audition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.27,0:21:41.36,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking about it now makes me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.40,0:21:44.79,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was frustrated, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.88,0:21:47.95,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.53,0:21:52.20,Italics,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If they hadn't become famous after that, \NI think I would've been content.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.20,0:21:56.54,Italics,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,But when I heard they'd be releasing their \Nfirst CD, I couldn't sit still anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.89,0:22:00.44,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, everything's going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.14,0:22:04.48,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I wasn't expecting \Nto lose someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.48,0:22:07.13,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,but I get more attention because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:12.18,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking about losing another \Nand becoming a solo act.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.18,0:22:14.11,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What? I'm too greedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.00,0:22:18.17,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.17,0:22:23.07,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,All I headed out to do was find \Nthe taxi I rode in then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.76,0:22:25.94,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I think I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.94,0:22:28.62,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a total coincidence. \NI must be lucky after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.94,0:22:28.91,sign_32271_317_Aozora_Comedy_Fe,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Aozora {\c&H599126&}Comedy {\c&H9273cf&}Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:30.34,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's going my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.89,0:22:32.92,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you more about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.69,0:22:36.92,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It'll go well again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.45,sign_32471_322_Uninstall__Zoode,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Uninstall "Zooden?" \N{\fs16\b0}All data will be erased \Nwhen this app is uninstalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.45,sign_32471_323_Cancel,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,Cancel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.29,0:22:36.45,sign_32471_324_Uninstall,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,Uninstall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.92,0:22:38.48,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Over the end of the year—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.51,0:22:41.79,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I'll tell you about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:44.05,sign_32666_327_Must_read_,SIGN PINK,0000,0000,0000,,Must-read!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.42,0:22:44.05,sign_32666_328_Foolproof_Method,SIGN ORANGE AND BLUE,0000,0000,0000,,Foolproof {\c&Hb75d49&}Methods {\c&H3d7ee7&}For {\c&Hb75d49&}Finding {\c&H3d7ee7&}a {\c&Hb75d49&}Job
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.70,0:22:45.92,Italics,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Will you make fried chicken \Nagain for me sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:51.82,Default,WADAGAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Like you said, I'm gonna do whatever it takes \Nto make my dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.01,0:22:59.20,Default,BOSS A,0000,0000,0000,,Kakihana, let's get lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.20,0:23:00.35,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.19,0:23:16.20,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.37,0:23:23.52,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Hop on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.13,0:23:29.54,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?